    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen starting nvim with \"-l\" option on mounted SSHFS directory, it gets stuck for about ~10 seconds before executing actual script.\nIssue is not reproduced when simply starting interactive nvim in the same directory.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ncreate any lua script\n```\necho 'print(\"hello from lua\")' > /tmp/test_min.lua\n```\nChange directory to some that is mounted via SSHFS\n```\ncd /mounted/sshfs/directory\n```\nRun following command\n```\nnvim --clean -u NONE -l /tmp/test_min.lua\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nnvim should execute script with minimal delay, <1s\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-452+g0976ce255b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDocker Container Fedora Linux 39\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nITerm2 3.6.10\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm\n\n### Installation\n\nRun via appimage from latest nightly release",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "After some investigation I discovered following.\nOutput of command\n```\nstrace -tt -T -f   -e trace=file,statfs,stat,getcwd,readlink   -o /tmp/timing.log   nvim --clean -u NONE -l /tmp/test_min.lua\n```\n\nIndicates that during startup nvim is constantly executing these syscalls\n```\n210   16:02:30.294128 readlinkat(AT_FDCWD, \"/mounted/workdir/my_user/vim\", 0xffffc2264000, 1023) = -1 ENOENT (No such file or directory) <0.103268>\n210   16:02:30.397648 getcwd(\"/mounted/workdir/my_user\", 4096) = 24 <0.000109>\n210   16:02:30.398766 getcwd(\"/mounted/workdir/my_user\", 1024) = 24 <0.000100>\n```\nAnd as `readlinkat` takes 100ms in this case, it adds up to 10s after tens of calls.\n\n[timing.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/27555660/timing.log)",
