        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> during startup nvim is constantly executing these syscalls\n\nalso `chdir`: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/21082 , https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/4855\n\nThis isn't really specific to `nvim -l`, unless you are expecting Nvim to be clever for that specific use-case.\n\nThere is probably an opportunity for improvement here, but it's an old problem: Vim startup expects the filesystem to be fast (or warm...), and is generally very naive.",
